Package: powerstats
Version: 1.0.0
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Depends: python3 (>= 3.10),
         python3-gi,
         python3-gi-cairo,
         gir1.2-gtk-4.0,
         gir1.2-adw-1,
         gir1.2-gdkpixbuf-2.0,
         python3-psutil,
         upower
Recommends: powertop
Maintainer: PowerStats Contributors <powerstats@example.com>
Homepage: https://github.com/powerstats/powerstats
Description: High-Fidelity Power Diagnostics and Analytics for Linux
 PowerStats is a native GTK4/Libadwaita application that explains your
 system's power consumption and application battery impact in plain
 human language rather than raw telemetry.
 .
 Features include:
  - Per-app battery drain with behavioral explanations
  - Last 24 Hours / 7 Days / 12 Month views
  - Interactive stacked bar charts
  - Intel RAPL hardware measurement support
  - Battery aging forecast via UPower
  - Background daemon with WAL-mode SQLite persistence
  - systemd user service for continuous data collection
